  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "What should I wear to prom?",
  "response": "Choosing an outfit for prom can be exciting but sometimes overwhelming. Here are some steps to guide you in making the best choice:\n\n1. **Dresses**: For individuals who prefer wearing dresses, there are several styles to consider:\n   - **Ball Gown**: Classic and elegant, perfect for a fairytale look.\n   - **Mermaid**: Form-fitting and flared at the bottom, ideal for creating a stunning silhouette.\n   - **A-Line**: This style is flattering for most body types and offers comfort.\n   - **Sheath**: Sleek and simple, great for a sophisticated look.\n   - **Two-Piece**: Trendy and youthful, it consists of a top and a separate skirt.\n\n   Colors can range from classic black and white to bold reds, blues, and metallics. Considering current trends like pastel hues or sequins might also be a good choice.\n\n2. **Suits or Tuxedos**: If you prefer wearing a suit or tuxedo:\n   - **Classic Tuxedo**: Timeless and sophisticated.\n   - **Modern Suit**: Customize with colors, patterns, and accessories for a trendy and personal look.\n   - **Colored Blazers**: For a bold statement, pair with neutral pants.\n   - **Velvet Jackets**: Luxurious and unique, often in rich colors.\n\n   Look into various accessories like bow ties, pocket squares, and cufflinks to complete the outfit.\n\n3. **Comfort**: Ensure your outfit is comfortable. Prom nights can be long, and comfort is key to enjoying the event.\n\n4. **Footwear**: Choosing the right shoes is important:\n   - For dresses: Heels, flats, or dressy sandals.\n   - For suits: Polished dress shoes like oxfords, loafers, or brogues.\n\n   Make sure your shoes are comfortable enough for dancing.\n\n5. **Accessories**: \n   - Jewelry (earrings, necklaces, bracelets) for added elegance.\n   - Clutch or small handbag to carry essentials.\n   - Corsages and boutonnieres if it\u2019s a tradition in your area.\n\n6. **Hair and Makeup**: Plan your hairstyle and makeup to complement your outfit. Consider professional services or practice in advance if you\u2019re doing it yourself.\n\nLastly, personal style and confidence are paramount. Choose what makes you feel amazing, and you'll surely shine at prom.",
